Package com.k2.Expressions.predicate

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Predicate
    The predicate interface extends the Expression interface for Boolean data type.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractPredicate
    This abstract class forms the basis of all the predicate classes
    PredicateAnd
    This predicate is a compound predicate and returns true if all the boolean expressions in it are true
    PredicateBetween
    The between predicate tests whether a comparable value is between a beginning and end value
    PredicateBuilder
    The predicate builder provides factory methods to create the different types of predicates
    PredicateEquals
    The equals predicate checks for equality between its arguments
    PredicateFalse
    The false predicate returns false
    PredicateGE
    The ge predicate checks whether a numeric value is greater than or equal to another numeric value
    PredicateGreaterThan
    The greater than predicate checks whether a comparable value is greater than another comparable value
    PredicateGreaterThanOrEqualTo
    The greater than or equals predicate checks whether the first comparable value is greater than or equal to the second comparable value
    PredicateGT
    The gt predicate checks whether the first numerical value is greater than the second numerical value
    PredicateIn
    The in predicate checks whether the first value is in the subsquent values
    PredicateIsFalse
    The is false predicate checks whether its given value is false
    PredicateIsTrue
    The is true predicate checks whether its given value is true
    PredicateLE
    The le predicate checks whether the first numerical value is less than or equal to the second numerical value
    PredicateLessThan
    The less than predicate checks whether the first comparable value is less than the second comparable value
    PredicateLessThanOrEqualTo
    The less than or equal to predicate checks whether the first comparable value is less than or equal to the second comparable value
    PredicateLike
    The like predicate checks whether the given string matches the given pattern
    PredicateLT
    The lt predicate checks whether the first numerical value is less than the second numerical value
    PredicateNot
    The not predicate negates its given boolean expression
    PredicateNotNull
    The not null predicate checks that the value of its argeuemnt is not null
    PredicateNull
    THe null predicate checks whether the value of its argument is null
    PredicateOr
    The or predicate is a compound predicate and returns true if any of the boolean expressions in it are true
    PredicateTrue
    The true predicate returns true
